  <p>
    Berriblue's work is very personal, with imagery surrounding
    mental health, personal identity, sexuality, and mortality.
  </p>

  <p>
    She works with raw, unfinished materials such as plywood,
    newsprint, packing paper, and bare ceramic, allowing the
    sensuality of the material to shine through.
  </p>

  <p>
    Though often quizzed on the meaning or inspiration behind
    specific imagery in her street art, she prefers to leave it
    open to the interpretation of the viewer.
  </p>

  <p class="section-quote">
    “Once I’ve put it out there, it no longer belongs to me.
    Whatever it means to you is correct.”
  </p>
{% endcall %}
